HEADWORD: Xanthophane
<hw>Xan"tho*phane</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Xantho-</ets> + Gr. <grk>fai`nein</grk> to show.]</ety>
<fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>The yellow pigment present in the inner
segments of the retina in animals. See <er>Chromophane</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Xanthophyll</ent>⟦br⟧
